column50: Overall, the Quality was good. Sometimes (especially for none technical users) it would have been better if it also explained the technical terms (like gradient boosting), as this might confuse people who are not familiar with those terms.

Although I'm not an expert on this topic I had the feeling the RAG system sometimes did not really answer the question that was asked and therefore could not be that helpful. Sometimes it was just way too long instead of giving direct answers. I still think it gave some good explanation for the model, but quite superficial, right? Could imagine that it acts like a quick "generate model summary" for people or "ask the model".
For me, the chatbot seems a bit too focused on sharing information it has - sometimes less is more. If interested or needed, there will be follow-up questions.
I would like to have the "Summary" at the top. For further details I can continue reading. Many of the answers are very detailed without benefit or even increasing confusion.
